raw_data.description: Your neighborhood headquarters for coffee, breakfast, lunch, dinner, ice cream, snack, pizza, bar, wine and good vibes!
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 2.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: Chicken ceaser wrap and fries were amazing
Wings slapped, great liquor selection, and great service!

Popular brunch spot for a reason! Busy & loud but we went on a Sat morning. Great vegan/vegetarian options. Vegan breakfast burrito is top notch. Best menu item is the egg & cheese biscuit. The biscuits are buttery Southern style just how Grandma makes. Coffee is good & they make a nice matcha latte. Definitely will be back when we return to the South!

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk
review_questions.Vegetarian offerings: Vegetarian menu or section, Clearly labeled vegetarian dishes
review_questions.Parking options: Free parking lot, Free street parking

reviews_data.review_text:
Do not recommend! Staff was confused and communication was horrible. They remade my order 3 times and still got it wrong. Once I tried to cash out my check I wasn’t even in the system.

When I got home I had seen 2 different charges on my card. One for 19.49 and then another for 31.76. I did not authorize these charges and on top of that they don’t have a phone number to contact them.

I don’t understand how a business like this has no contact info. Very disappointing, food was okey nothing special. Management had no communication skills and clearly don’t care about there customers especially after been extremely patient with them and giving them the benefit of doubt. But could not even make a bacon, egg and cheese sandwich correctly.
Great addition to the neighborhood. Great coffee, solid selection of beers, well made cocktails & solid food.

Good place for coffee and food. Giving it 4 stars because of atmosphere: everything is yellow, music is loud (even in the morning) and lights are very bright. If they toned things down it would be much more relaxing
All of their wraps are great!

Spotty wifi and cold coffee - I live in the neighborhood and needed a place to work when I lost power. I figured that since this place is brand new they would have invested in good technology. The woman taking my order said it had been "spotty", which really meant non-functional. I decided to get a coffee and try it anyway. Coffee was cold. Considering the bad experience I had at the Elizabeth location, I doubt I will be back.

Great café/cafeteria spot. They do close a little early, but have good coffee and food and the workers are always relaxed and friendly. Nice place to get some work done. Occasional issues with WiFi access.

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Dietary restrictions, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Super friendly staff/bartenders. Great drinks, amazing food. Tons of gluten friendly options
We had the chicken avocado wrap and the spicy Italian. They were both very good. The atmosphere is fairly loud but a quiter area towards the back is nice. The outside area is really nice.
Great spot to meet friends for lunch,  drink or snack.  After the meet up,  go for a walk around and amazing neighborhood.
Great spot. We have been a few times, food and service is always awesome.

review_questions.Seating type: Indoor dining area, Bar area, Outdoor patio / terrace, Booth seating, Counter seating

reviews_data.review_text: Great addition to Myers Park.  We were very excited for it to open.  My side salad and chicken salad were extremely fresh.   The chicken salad is absolutely delicious.  Everyone is very kind and helpful.

Walked over to grab an iced matcha this morning at the new PM location in Myer’s Park. The barista nailed my order and was helpful with offering me lightly sweetened options.

The space itself is open and clean with indoor and outdoor seating options. I’ll have to come back to try their food. I have my eye on the pizzas. Also saw that they serve Two Scoops ice cream!

This is my go to Cafe/"Market"
Best Cortado around.
Try the "Went Out Last Night Burger" !

So far a good addition to the MP neighborhood. Had a nice breakfast burrito, but some of the other food items could be less greasy like the pizza and smash burgers. Judging by the crowd the lighter the better.
Love this place. Been a customer since their location on East Blvd in Dilworth. Followed them to Elizabeth, but SO happy they opened a location in Myers Park!

review_questions.null: Vegetarian options, Parking, Kid-friendliness, Wheelchair accessibility

reviews_data.review_text: Very cute location! Spacious patio and family/dog friendly. The food was excellent and their drinks were particurarly delicious. I will be back soon!

Love the new location! Our favorites are the chicken avocado wrap, hipster salad (I like to add shrimp), and my husband is a big fan of the burger! Super kid friendly with chicken tenders - possibly the best in Charlotte. Highly recommend adding it to your local routine.

Elizabeth Location Only - (since they fail to respond to customer’s concerns) I guess the only way to reach this place is to leave a one star review. I’ve tried calling, messaging on IG and the contact tab on your website and still no response. On last Friday, I paid for two orders of kids chicken tenders between 3:00-3:30 via an online order. The chicken tenders were not edible and basically burnt. All I want is my money back for the meal that I paid for. If someone could actually respond to a customer’s request that would be nice.
I checked this new location out over the weekend! The service and atmosphere were great! So happy they are finally open! Natalie was wonderful!

Visited People’s Market on 6/8, just one week into them being open. The space is very cute and has ample seating inside and outside. I ordered the Market Bagel and it was DELICIOUS. I also got a plain cold brew and it was very good. My partner got Peoples Market Platter and thought the bacon was a standout. Can’t wait to come back for a different meal time!

reviews_data.review_text: Went for lunch today. Great food, fast service and nice staff!
